<p>CONFIDENTIAL</p>

<p>My telegram No. 825. [2] In reply to formal note Secretary of State has today advised me [3] that appointment of Minister to take charge all affairs relating to Australia is entirely acceptable to the United States Government and that President [4] will accord formal recognition at convenience of His Majesty [5] and His Majestyâ€™s Government in the Commonwealth of Australia.</p>

<p>LOTHIAN</p>

<p>_</p>

<p>1 Another copy of this cablegram gives the date and time of dispatch as 7 December 1939, 10.45 p.m. (on file FA: AA1975/5, 1939, Australia-Representation (Dipl.) in Washington).</p>

<p>2 Not printed.</p>

<p>3 The note was in fact sent by the Acting Secretary of State, Sumner Welles, on 6 December 1939 (see PRO: FO 372/3319).</p>

<p>4 Franklin D. Roosevelt.</p>

<p>5 King George VI.</p>

